<div id="review_3801427785" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3801427785" />
    <a title="Andrew Blankenship" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/41220647-andrew-blankenship"><img alt="Andrew Blankenship" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1611804380p2/41220647.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3801427785?book_show_action=true">Jan 27, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Andrew Blankenship" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Andrew Blankenship" href="/user/show/41220647-andrew-blankenship">Andrew Blankenship</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781937929183" href="/book/show/18160656-the-wide-game">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3801427785" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1407760879746619704">A masterly woven tale that draws on the best of the 1980s slasher films. Full of memorable and genuinely frightening moments.<br/><br/>While the first two thirds of the book would have made a perfect horror/slasher movie, the third part of the book is where the writing really shined. I&apos;ve often sat there in a darkened theater while the credits rolled, wondering what happened to the characters and how they dealt with the trauma that would have left them scarred for the rest of their lives.<br/><br/>Overall, one of t</span>
  <span id="freeText1407760879746619704" style="display:none">A masterly woven tale that draws on the best of the 1980s slasher films. Full of memorable and genuinely frightening moments.<br /><br />While the first two thirds of the book would have made a perfect horror/slasher movie, the third part of the book is where the writing really shined. I've often sat there in a darkened theater while the credits rolled, wondering what happened to the characters and how they dealt with the trauma that would have left them scarred for the rest of their lives.<br /><br />Overall, one of the best crafted horror books I have ever read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1407760879746619704" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


