        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1780386437" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8796760912675477935">Great book from Michael West. The Wide Game meshes some evil dead and children of the corn vibes together for a great atmosphere (the story is not anything like the above mentioned titles however). West&apos;s story is set in the 80&apos;s for the most part and has you feeling like your watching an old slasher, but with a way better story. Not to mention he throws quite a few twists in there that I genuinly didn&apos;t see coming at all. This is a perfect starting point for his Harmony, Indiana series and I&apos;m </span>
  <span id="freeText8796760912675477935" style="display:none">Great book from Michael West. The Wide Game meshes some evil dead and children of the corn vibes together for a great atmosphere (the story is not anything like the above mentioned titles however). West's story is set in the 80's for the most part and has you feeling like your watching an old slasher, but with a way better story. Not to mention he throws quite a few twists in there that I genuinly didn't see coming at all. This is a perfect starting point for his Harmony, Indiana series and I'm proud to say I live in Indy and this book makes me think twice about stepping into any cornfields...</span>
